Fidelity National Sells Flood Insurance Unit for $154 Million

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-07-13T12:06:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/fidelity-national-sells-flood-insurance-unit-for-154-million.html
Fidelity National Financial Inc. (FNF) ,
the largest U.S. title insurer, said it agreed to sell its
business providing flood coverage to WRM America Holdings LLC
for $210 million.  Fidelity expects to record a gain of about $154 million
before tax on the sale, the Jacksonville, Florida-based company
said today in a statement distribute by PR Newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 Bsutherland5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  